caption.text:
You next?

Am I promising you 300,000 by the end of the year? Of course not. Everyone’s growth journey is different, but here’s the thing, you have to actually START your journey if you want to hit your goals ♥️

I started my growth journey 8 months ago, just hit 300k and I’ve helped 1000s of students start theirs as well. 🥹

IS IT YOU NEXT?!
Comment “GUIDE” below to grab my Instagram Growth Guide, it’s a simple breakdown on how the algorithm works, and how you can get it working for you.

What students are saying about my Growth Guide 👀

thank you for your incredible guide. It has given me the confidence to delve into a world I am totally unfamiliar with. Not only that, it has given me the structure I need to build out a strategy and a plan for tackling our social pages, instead of feeling around in the dark!

#iggrowth #instagramgrowth #contentstrategy #contentideas

caption.text:
Make a Reminder Post ⬇️

This secret Instagram feature is so clever! Instagram can actually send reminders of the event at the time or date mentioned! 

I used this on my last launch and it was a fantastic help notifying my followers at the scheduled time and date. This effect is so versatile you could use it to highlight any date or event, for business or just a birthday coming up!

Don’t forget to save this post so you don’t forget the steps! 

- Tap and begin a new story, choose any image you would like to share, and press next. Go to your sparkles tab, and look for the filter “falling down cards” if you don’t find it, I’ve saved it to this post. 

- Now go to sticker again, type Polaroid and choose your favourite frame to place on screen, then sticker tab again and look for the countdown option, select this you can choose any date or time you’d like and add a title announcing what you are counting down to.

- Place the countdown icon onto the white rectangle when clicked, this will actually notify your audience of the event at the time specified.

- Now add text stickers to match the theme of your announcement, I am using coming soon you could use anything you would like.

If you like this tutorial, make sure you’re following me I add new tips daily and can’t wait to help you on your Instagram growth journey!

I really hope this design helps, but if you’re looking for more support on your Instagram growth journey, type the word GUIDE below and I’ll send you a link to my 50 page growth guide I wrote you through the Instagram growth process step-by-step!

#instagramgrowth #instagramgorbusiness
#instagramtips

caption.text:
Do these 3 things to grow⬇️

The no1 complaint I hear when it comes growth…

“Only my followers see my posts”…. Well, if you want to start reaching non followers, which you MUST do to grow, you need to remember these 3 things.

Save this post so you don’t forget 

- create shareable or saveable content
an audience needs a reason to follow you or engage with you, if you can become useful or valuable to them, you will earn their engagement. Remember value comes in lots of forms, it can be tips, tricks, it can be relatable situations, or even motivational. Always ask yourself before you post- what’s in this for THEM.

- get your watch time up
instagram will push your content out further if audiences are consuming it until the end. I don’t mean using spamming 1 second reel tactics, I mean keep it interesting, create curiosity, include movement, and try playing with different lengths of reels too.

- start conversations and ask for comments
Often we expect people to comment on our posts, but we can forget to initiate that. So go ahead and ask questions in your captions and comments, create interesting and engaging posts.

Lastly, having the right caption to stop the scroll can really help too! Comment HOOKS below and I’ll share 100 captions with you for free.

#instagramgrowth #iggrowth #reelsideas #reelstips

caption.text:
Step by step instructions below ⬇️ 

This story idea is a great way to showcase your products, images from your brand or any 4 photos you’d like to share. I’m using holiday images, but anything would work! 

First SAVE this reel so you don’t forget the steps! And maybe even share with someone else who loves to create!

- tap to begin a new story post, select camera, tap the layout button and choose the 4 photo layout 

- Add any 4 images you would like to share and tap save 

- Now go to new story again, camera, and scroll across the bottom of the screen until you get the magnifying glass- in here type “photobooth scroll v2” and tap the bookmark icon to save 

- Now begin a new story again, use the 4 images layout you made earlier, tap the sparkles icon and use the photobooth filter you just saved 

- Now go to text to, I used the last font, with black background and typed . With 15 spaces, place in centre of the screen.

- now go to sticker tab, the cutout feature and make a sticker from one of your images, place that in the black space.

- now add any text to suit, I added 2024 vibes, using an orange for a zero but any text to suit theme of you post to showcase your images.

If you love this instagram story idea, check out some of my others and make sure you’re following me, I share new ones daily to help you grow and learn on your instagram journey! 

If you haven’t yet, you might want to grab my Instagram growth guide, the simple strategy to see growth in your account! 

#socialmediahelp #socialmediamarketing #socialmediagrowth #instagramgrowthtips #reelsideas #reelsinspo #storyidea

text_info_list.text: An Instagram Secret, I bet you didn’t know

caption.text:
I’ve been a busy bee 🐝 

I know Instagram can feel exhausting when you don’t know what to post, who to listen to or what to do- well I’m working on my newest product, this is going to be a full course breaking down every step you need to follow to go from confused to clear. 

There will be videos, worksheets, templates and tips! Everything you need on your Instagram journey, if you join my waitlist now, you will hear about it first, and be able to grab the early bird pricing before the course goes on general release 

#iggrowth #instagramgrowth #contentcreator #contentstrategy

caption.text:
Share if you can relate 😫

It can be hard being seen and heard on Instagram, standing out amongst the thousands of other accounts, but I want you to know I’m here to support you! I’m just working on my own online course, packed full of video, worksheets and templates for you to use on your own account

Just comment REGISTER below to be added to the waitlist when I launch. Getting on this list easily will give you access to early bird pricing too! 

#instagramgrowthtips #instagramgrowth #iggrowth #contentcreator #contentstrategy #smallbusiness #smallbusinessowner

caption.text:
1 photo announcement story ⬇️

This is one of the most SIMPLE instagram stories you will ever create, you only need one photo and instagram will do the rest! ⬇️
I’m all about working smarter, not harder.

Don’t forget to save this post so you don’t forget the steps!

Here is the step by step guide below:

- go to start a new story, tap create, and select GIF.

- Type in Fundo circle, and use the same filter as me and press next

- now go to your stickers tab, photo, add any photo that you would like to share, tap to make a circle and place in the centre of the screen.

- Now go to your stickers tab, type neon circle, use the sticker I have and place it over the top of your image and the background.

- Go to sticker tab once more, look for the link sticker, and from here you can add the link of your business your brand your shop, your blog or anything that you would like to share this on screen

- Go to your stickers tab again, type in neon click choose your favourite sticker and place it right on top of the link. Anybody that taps this will get taken straight through to the link you provided.

- You sent the text tab, I use the last font from here. You can add any text that you wish, I added shop now but you can use whatever will suit your post, place it right on screen.

If you found this post useful, make sure you’re following me I post new tips daily to help you on your Instagram growth journey!

Want more tips!? I recorded my entire Live masterclass, it’s 75 minutes long and jam packed with instagram tips and advice as well my entire growth strategy- just comment CLASS below and I’ll whiz it your way 

#instagramtips #instagramgorbusiness #instagramgrowth

clips_metadata.reusable_text_attribute_string: An Instagram Secret, I bet you didn’t know

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram Secret, I bet you didn’t know

caption.text:
You know I don’t gatekeep here ⬇️

There’s a brand-new Instagram feature that’s gonna really help inspire you when it comes to creating and posting on your account.

Save this post so you don’t forget, and maybe share with a friend who might want to know.

Follow the steps above, and never run out of ideas again! 

- Go to your professional dashboard, click this and look for the inspiration tab.

- Now look for the real tab at the top of the page, click this and you’ll be shown different categories of content.

This is a great place to start when planning your own content. You will find lots of inspiration on this page, but if you want to WHAT and WHY and the the strategy and on how to grow your account specifically, I have a 75 minute video lesson which you will love!

Just comment the word CLASS below and I’ll share it with you!

#iggrowth #contentstrategy #instagramgrowth #newfeature

caption.text:
Try this to increase connection!

Summer is a difficult time to grow and sell on Instagram, people are away and their priority right now might not be buying. However….its a great time to think about nurturing relationships, connection and building trust!

I was inspired by @shannonmckinstrie and decided to make my own version, I’d love you to send this reel to yourself, then use the audio to make your own version for your audience!

#relateable #smallbusiness #smallbusinessowner #contentstrategy

caption.text:
Hack to Share a Reel ⬇️

Instagram has confirmed that reels are the still the best way for you to reach new followers , but stories are the best way to connect to audiences….well this hack combines both, AND looks great too!

Don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps!! 

- add an image to your story, move the image over to the right hand side of the screen leaving space on the left.

- go to your text tab, and add any words you’d like to use to describe the reel. And copy paste to fill the space. Move the words to the left hand side of the screen. And save this image.

- Go to the reel, you would like to share, tap the aeroplane and share to story. Now go to sticker tab, photo album and add the saved image.

- go to sticker tab, type iPhone frame, and add iPhone to cover the text you added.

- now hold down and slide down to move the reel on top of the saved image. Place reel inside the frame.

- Now go to your stickers, tab, type new reel, choose your favourite, and place it on the screen

Anybody that taps your reel is going to get taken through to watch it. 

If you love this instagram reel idea, check out some of my others and make sure you’re following me, I share new ones every single day to help you on your instagram growth journey!

But remember if you want some more detailed help on how to grow your Instagram audience, comment GUIDE below and I’ll send over a link to the strategy I wrote myself which has gained me 280,000 followers this year 🚀

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram Secret, I bet you didnt know…

caption.text:
Tell don’t just SELL

I can’t make this clear enough, nothing turns people off quicker than being hard sold to with every post you make. Not ALL posts need to outright sell you, your offer or your product.

I want you to remember “tell don’t sell”
Tell me something, don’t just sell me something!

I’m writing about this in great depth in my brand new course, “Embrace” your instagram, comment REGISTER below to join the waitlist and grab a discount when I launch!

#instagramgrowthexpert #contentcreator #contentstrategy 

Did you know this?

caption.text:
increase watch time ⬇️

This is a brand new Instagram feature that’s going to increase watch time and curiosity effect within your audience! Watchtime is a metric instagram measures when ranking content, and is key to instagram growth, try this simple trick to increase your audience watchtime!

First off don’t forget to SAVE this post, so you don’t forget the steps

- tap and begin a new a new story, choose any image you’d like to share, go to your text tab, select first font and do full stop with black background on, resize sheer black cover to fill screen. And save this image.

- Now go to your sticker tab, type firework and add fireworks to the dark image you saved

- Now go to sticker tab, Choose the frame option, and add any single image you would like to share, you can add text or caption into the space under the frame. Now anybody who wants to reveal the image will need to shake their phone, or tap the screen.

- This is clever as it will increase the time of your audience and encourage them to engage with your content. This is crucial when it comes to Instagram growth. You could use for any announcement or launch or to increase engagement with your audience! 

If you like this tip, make sure you’re following me I add new ones daily! I’ve helped hundreds of you here with my growth guide, and can’t wait to help even more of you grow and understand what instagram is all about! 

If you want a little more support, and a simple instagram growth strategy to follow, Comment below GUIDE and I’ll send you a link to mine! I’ve grown over 1.2 million followers so far!

#instagramgrowth #instagramforbusiness #instagramtips
